<p>I learned static method today, and I am confused about how values change inside the static method.  When I write static method like this </p>  <pre><code>public class test{ public static int printInt(int t,int n){ System.out.println(t); t= t + n; return n; } } </code></pre>  <p>and call it in main</p>  <pre><code>public class Method { public static int i; public static int m; public static void main(String[] args){     i = 5;     m = 6;      test.printInt(i,m);     System.out.println(i); } } </code></pre>  <p>the t do not change as I suppose to. If the static method only make change into values that you return?</p>